OL,6,F"They would have still had a lovely
OL,7,FChristmas. It was a time to bring all
OL,8,Fthe family together. They would have
OL,9,Fbeen singing carols around the piano,
OL,10,Fso they would've had a great time."
OL,12,FThe history of Mr Straw's house
OL,14,FIn 1923 grocer William Straw moved
OL,15,Fwith his wife, Florence, and two sons
OL,16,Ffrom the flat above their shop to the
OL,17,Fsemi-detached property, number 7 Blyth
OL,18,FGrove.
