OL,3,CChristmas inside time capsule house
OL,4,Cleft untouched since 1920s
OL,6,FMrs Straw chose wallpaper, curtains
OL,7,Fand an Egyptian-inspired carpet of the
OL,8,Ftime to decorate the house alongside
OL,9,Fornaments, elegant glassware and new
OL,10,FFrench doors.
OL,12,FWhen Mr Straw died suddenly in 1932,
OL,13,Fas a show of respect, the family kept
OL,14,Fhis personal belongings in place,
OL,15,Fincluding his coats and hats.
OL,17,FThe 1932 calendar in the front room
OL,18,Fwas never removed and his pipes and
OL,19,Ftobacco were left hanging by the
OL,20,Ffireplace in the dining room.
